<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="1959" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="17.[160,1156,1422,1585]" box="[160,276,1422,1447]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1959">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,276,1422,1447]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="1959">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[160,1156,1422,1585]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1959">
This species differs from the other known species of the subgenus in the surstylus large, deeply bilobed subbasally, with six small prensisetae on inner surface (
<figureCitation box="[976,1082,1492,1516]" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="18.[160,225,883,906]" captionTargetBox="[163,1152,143,852]" captionTargetId="figure-277@18.[163,1153,142,852]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 11. Stegana (Oxyphortica) dehiscens Cheng and Chen, sp. nov., male terminalia. (a) epandrium, cercus and surstylus (lateral view); (b) surstylus (ventral view); (c, d) hypandrium, parameres gonopods, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme (ventral and lateral views). Scale lines = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5182877" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5182877/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="1959">Figure 11</figureCitation>
(a, b)), the gonopods sclerotized basally, anterodistally membranous and bearing dense hair on the inner surface (
<figureCitation box="[369,475,1561,1585]" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="18.[160,225,883,906]" captionTargetBox="[163,1152,143,852]" captionTargetId="figure-277@18.[163,1153,142,852]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 11. Stegana (Oxyphortica) dehiscens Cheng and Chen, sp. nov., male terminalia. (a) epandrium, cercus and surstylus (lateral view); (b) surstylus (ventral view); (c, d) hypandrium, parameres gonopods, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme (ventral and lateral views). Scale lines = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5182877" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5182877/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="1959">Figure 11</figureCitation>
(c, d)).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="18" lastPageNumber="1960" pageId="17" pageNumber="1959" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="17.[160,1155,1633,1727]" box="[160,294,1633,1658]" pageId="17" pageNumber="1959">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,294,1633,1658]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="1959">Description</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[160,1155,1633,1727]" lastBlockId="18.[160,1156,1045,1311]" lastPageId="18" lastPageNumber="1960" pageId="17" pageNumber="1959">
Clypeus and palpus dark brown. Mesoscutum nearly brown. Katepisternum brownish above, yellow below. Scutellum brown, yellow along margin. Wing fuscous anteriorly, pale posteriorly. All abdominal tergites brown in male, black except two basal ones yellow in female. Sternites yellow in male, dark brown to black in female. Male terminalia: Epandrium undeveloped on posterolateral corners, with dense pubescence and setae (
<figureCitation box="[529,641,1149,1173]" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="18.[160,225,883,906]" captionTargetBox="[163,1152,143,852]" captionTargetId="figure-277@18.[163,1153,142,852]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 11. Stegana (Oxyphortica) dehiscens Cheng and Chen, sp. nov., male terminalia. (a) epandrium, cercus and surstylus (lateral view); (b) surstylus (ventral view); (c, d) hypandrium, parameres gonopods, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme (ventral and lateral views). Scale lines = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5182877" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5182877/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="1960">Figure 11</figureCitation>
(a)). Cercus lacking pubescence (
<figureCitation box="[1042,1155,1149,1173]" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="18.[160,225,883,906]" captionTargetBox="[163,1152,143,852]" captionTargetId="figure-277@18.[163,1153,142,852]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 11. Stegana (Oxyphortica) dehiscens Cheng and Chen, sp. nov., male terminalia. (a) epandrium, cercus and surstylus (lateral view); (b) surstylus (ventral view); (c, d) hypandrium, parameres gonopods, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme (ventral and lateral views). Scale lines = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5182877" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5182877/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="1960">Figure 11</figureCitation>
(a)). Surstylus with numerous setae on outer surface (
<figureCitation box="[792,901,1183,1207]" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="18.[160,225,883,906]" captionTargetBox="[163,1152,143,852]" captionTargetId="figure-277@18.[163,1153,142,852]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 11. Stegana (Oxyphortica) dehiscens Cheng and Chen, sp. nov., male terminalia. (a) epandrium, cercus and surstylus (lateral view); (b) surstylus (ventral view); (c, d) hypandrium, parameres gonopods, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme (ventral and lateral views). Scale lines = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5182877" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5182877/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="1960">Figure 11</figureCitation>
(a)). Parameres fused, with a few sensilla per side (
<figureCitation box="[518,631,1218,1242]" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="18.[160,225,883,906]" captionTargetBox="[163,1152,143,852]" captionTargetId="figure-277@18.[163,1153,142,852]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 11. Stegana (Oxyphortica) dehiscens Cheng and Chen, sp. nov., male terminalia. (a) epandrium, cercus and surstylus (lateral view); (b) surstylus (ventral view); (c, d) hypandrium, parameres gonopods, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme (ventral and lateral views). Scale lines = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5182877" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5182877/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="1960">Figure 11</figureCitation>
(c, d)). Aedeagus nearly membranous, with dense pubescence (
<figureCitation box="[397,508,1253,1277]" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="18.[160,225,883,906]" captionTargetBox="[163,1152,143,852]" captionTargetId="figure-277@18.[163,1153,142,852]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 11. Stegana (Oxyphortica) dehiscens Cheng and Chen, sp. nov., male terminalia. (a) epandrium, cercus and surstylus (lateral view); (b) surstylus (ventral view); (c, d) hypandrium, parameres gonopods, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme (ventral and lateral views). Scale lines = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5182877" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5182877/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="1960">Figure 11</figureCitation>
(c, d)). Gonopods broadened anteriorly, laterally fused with hypandrium (
<figureCitation box="[383,494,1287,1311]" captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="18.[160,225,883,906]" captionTargetBox="[163,1152,143,852]" captionTargetId="figure-277@18.[163,1153,142,852]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 11. Stegana (Oxyphortica) dehiscens Cheng and Chen, sp. nov., male terminalia. (a) epandrium, cercus and surstylus (lateral view); (b) surstylus (ventral view); (c, d) hypandrium, parameres gonopods, aedeagus and aedeagal apodeme (ventral and lateral views). Scale lines = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5182877" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5182877/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="1960">Figure 11</figureCitation>
(e)).
</paragraph>
